From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 2026 21:44:42 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] ==== sis overflow fix ====

mm/damon/core: use overflow-immune jiffies helpers for sis comparisons

DAMON uses normal comparison operators for passed_sample_intervals and
*_sis counts.  When overflows to passed_sample_intervals happen,
therefore, the event could happen unexpectedly frequently for a
duration.

Let's say aggregation_interval 100ms, sampling_interval 5ms,
and next_aggregation_sis ULONG_MAX - 3.  Once passed_sample_intervals
reach ULONG_MAX - 3, the aggregation is executed.  And
next_aggregation_sis becomes 2.  In the next aggregation, because
passed_sample_intervals (ULONG_MAX - 2) >= next_aggregation_sis (2),
aggregation happens.  Again in the next iteration, and so on, until
passed_sample_intervals also overflows and be same to
next_aggregation_sis.

It takes at least one sampling interval between the
passed_sample_intervals increase.  The interval is 5ms by default, and
usually [auto-]tuned for hundreds of milliseconds.  That means it takes
248 days or 4,971 days to have the overflow on 32 bit machines if the
sampling interval is 5ms and 100ms, respectively.  On 64 bit machines,
the numbers become 2924712086.77536 and 58494241735.5072 years.  So the
real user impact is negligible.

Similar thing happens for all *_sis counters including
next_ops_update_sis, next_intervals_tune_sis, and next_apply_sis.  Fix
this

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_moxc1kxq | 0
 1 file changed, 0 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_moxc1kxq

diff --git a/hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_moxc1kxq b/hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_moxc1kxq
